This paper is primarily focused on the security of operating system kernels, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of formal verification methods, which is a topic in both operating systems (cs.OS) and software engineering (cs.SE). The paper also mentions the use of annotations, which is a topic in programming languages (cs.PL) and the use of automated methods, which is a topic in logic in computer science (cs.LO).
